// Material: M_MetaHuman_Variation_Master
// Description: Master material for MetaHuman character variations

/*
This master material provides the foundation for all character variations in the game.
It integrates with the MetaHuman framework while adding prehistoric-specific customizations.

Material Properties:
- Shading Model: Default Lit
- Blend Mode: Opaque
- Two Sided: False

Key Parameters:

FACE VARIATION:
- FaceVariation01 (Scalar): Controls facial structure blend (0-1)
- FaceVariation02 (Scalar): Controls facial features blend (0-1)
- FaceVariation03 (Scalar): Controls facial proportions (0-1)

SKIN PROPERTIES:
- SkinTone (Scalar): Controls skin color variation (0-1)
  * 0.0 = Pale/Light
  * 0.5 = Medium
  * 1.0 = Dark
- SkinRoughness (Scalar): Surface roughness for weathered appearance
- SubsurfaceScattering (Scalar): Skin translucency

EYE CUSTOMIZATION:
- EyeColor (Scalar): Eye color variation (0-1)
  * 0.0-0.2 = Brown variants
  * 0.3-0.6 = Hazel/Green variants
  * 0.7-1.0 = Blue/Gray variants
- EyeWetness (Scalar): Eye surface moisture

HAIR PROPERTIES:
- HairVariation (Scalar): Hair color and style variation
- HairDirtiness (Scalar): Adds grime and weathering to hair

WEATHERING & AGING:
- AgeSpots (Scalar): Age-related skin variations
- DirtOverlay (Scalar): Environmental dirt and grime
- ScarVisibility (Scalar): Controls scar prominence
- TattooVisibility (Scalar): Controls tattoo opacity

CLOTHING INTEGRATION:
- ClothingMask (Texture): Defines clothing coverage areas
- ClothingColor (Vector3): Base clothing color
- ClothingWear (Scalar): Wear and tear on clothing

ENVIRONMENTAL ADAPTATION:
- WeatherExposure (Scalar): Sun damage and exposure effects
- MudStains (Texture): Procedural mud and dirt stains
- BloodStains (Scalar): Combat-related blood effects

Material Graph Structure:

BaseColor Output:
SkinTone → ColorLerp → DirtOverlay → AgeSpots → FinalBaseColor

Normal Output:
MetaHumanNormal → ScarNormal → WeatheringNormal → FinalNormal

Roughness Output:
BaseSkinRoughness → AgeRoughness → DirtRoughness → FinalRoughness

This material system ensures visual consistency while providing extensive
customization options for the procedural character variation system.
*/